I really wanted some tacos and researched this place because it was open past 10. Menu looked great, so I was excited to try some things out. To start, I enjoyed one of the handmade drinks...the Pilsen Jamaica (I believe that was the name, definitely had Jamaica in it). It was delicious and strong. For my meal, I ended up getting some queso fundido with chorizo. I wish there was a bit more chorizo served with the dish. The cheese overpowered it a bit. I'm a huge fundido fan and it was a bit too much cheese for me and not enough meat. Tacos wise, I tried the charrito which is one of their most popular along with the carne asada. Carne asada was my fav. It had a hint of spice that I absolutely loved. I also ordered a side of rice and beans that were pretty good as well.  Overall, the experience was decent. I wasn't raving about it, but I also didn't hate it.  And just a little sidenote: the kitchen closes at 10:30 on weekdays (not sure if it's the same for weekends). So I'm glad I got there early enough to order some food.

My boyfriend and I were originally going to try Los Comales but I saw this place on yelp and we decided to go for a more modern Mexican cuisine for date night. We were able to find parking across the street fairly quickly.  We ordered mango margaritas which were delicious. Perfect portion of tequila and mango mixer.  Chips and salsa are given for free. The chips were nice and crunchy. We got the elote with lime and chili which was delicious. We ordered the carne asada taco, pescado taco and the al pastor. My favorite was the pescado taco. The cod was perfectly fried and the sauce that was poured on top was a perfect balance between spicy and sweet.  My boyfriend liked the carne asada taco because it had a hint of spice with a balance of caramalized red onions.

Work-in-Progress, casual DATE VENUE. Common Ingredients prepared well in temp and balance of ingredients.  CAUTION: Bar setup in NOT optimized for fast service in a way that drinks are prepared at the back end and ingredients are up front. Therefore, DO NOT expect your drinks to come sooner, but later it will show up. *Lol*  Single/Small ELOTE LA MEJIKANA 🌽 is the same as Street Vendors. Here, you can get it ANY time of day, with more cheese and balance of ingredients.  It's $0.50-0.75 difference from the Street Vendors w/ taste guaranty.  HITS the Spot doesn't it?  $3.50 LOMITO PLANCHADO TAQUITO/TACO (& Pescado) is the only worthy tack on the list.  Ribeye was dry in nature, but not overcooked. Appreciate the Blue Corn Tortilla!  Apple is MIA!  18-pcs of halved LANGOSTINOS 🦐 has worthy praises!  Bread or Rice comes with it. If you eat with gusto (photo attached), you can make 3 meals (2 from Langostinos w/ side dishes of bread or rice, +1 from the sauce itself as a dip/condiment to Korean Enoki Omelette Pancake).  One and only dessert, CHURROS. Forget the overloaded cinammon sugar. Meh on CHURROS.  Caramel with goat milk is the Star! ✨🌟 Suggested plating: (1) stack the CHURROS, (2) 2 separate small containers for Star Caramel, & Cinnamon Sugar.  Fruits can have their pile as well, or wherever it lands on the plate.  🍸🍻🍾🍷DRINKS -- Impressive boiled flower, JAMAICA.  Less ice, HORCHATA is the creamiest, smooth & best price of them all (can you make it hot and/or mix with coffee for perfect drink with dessert?). LOVE LOVE the flight of ALL MEXICAN BEERS! (Or, beer brands preferred by Mexicans). Choose wisely on COCKTAILS/TEY QUIRISI - I think 2 Booze Cocktails 👍👍 are worthy compared to Booze+Juice 😐.  Slow SERVICE is the norm for the neighborhood. Great for Dates. Bad, when it's a busy night

My friend and I ordered chips and guacamole to start the process. The chips were good but I felt that the guacamole could be improved. Try mincing the jalapenos up instead of serving them as half round slices. The tomatoes were a bit large too but everyone has their own style. I did feel like the guacamole could be much more spicy. Entre: I forgot what the name of the entire was but it said it had Chile de Árbol con Nuez sauce. I know this chile to be super spicy with a hint of maybe peanut butter, but my sandwich tasted nothing like it. I had to ask for more of the sauce. When it arrived, I grabbed a chip and it still did not taste spicy at all. My friend also agreed that it was not spicy.  Lastly, my friend and I both ordered an alcoholic beverage and we weren't asked to show an ID while other people, who I assume are older than me, were asked to show it. Did the server forget to ask or do I look old enough to pass as an adult?
